<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-07-14T11:15:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-07-14T11:15:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Draper</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-07-14T17:15:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 14,
                                        1897—5.15 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your dispatch of the 22d (ultimo) relating to meat has been received. It
                            may help me to know, by telegraph, which European countries do not
                            require consular visé with shipments of meat.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Draper.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>